Description: Implements a model-based approach for determining optimal item subsets 
    that maximize the predictive validity of test scores with respect to external 
    variables. The methodology is based on Item Response Theory (IRT) and linear 
    factor analysis, using Confirmatory Factor Analysis (CFA) for item calibration 
    and bootstrap procedures for empirical validation. The package provides both 
    computational functions and an interactive Shiny application for ease of use.
